com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.processors

Class PropertyRenderingViewProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.processors.EntityViewProcessorAdapter
      • com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.processors.PropertyRenderingViewProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EntityViewProcessor

    @Component
 @Exposed
 @Scope(value="prototype")
public class PropertyRenderingViewProcessor
extends EntityViewProcessorAdapter
    Renders one or more registered properties from the EntityPropertyRegistry attached to the EntityViewContext. As these are entity properties, the ControlNamePrefixingPostProcessor will be added when generating the elements for these properties.

    This processor will first create a Map of ViewElementBuilders for all properties requested. These will not be added to the general builderMap however, but will be available as a ViewElementBuilderMap under the attribute ATTRIBUTE_PROPERTY_BUILDERS in the EntityView. Following processors can update the builder collection.

    During render(EntityViewRequest, EntityView, ContainerViewElementBuilderSupport, ViewElementBuilderMap, ViewElementBuilderContext), the actual ViewElements will get created and added to the container. If the global builderMap contains a builder named ATTRIBUTE_PROPERTIES_CONTAINER_BUILDER the elements will get added to that builder, else they will get added to the container passed as argument.

    This processor will prefix all properties having an EntityAttributes.NATIVE_PROPERTY_DESCRIPTOR attribute to have their control names prefixed.

    Since:
    2.0.0
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
